Video-Filename

This module parses information about a video file from the filename.  Things
like name/season/episode/episode_name/extension for TV shows, and name/date for
movies.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Video::Filename

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Video-Filename

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Video-Filename

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Video-Filename

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Video-Filename


